In recognition of National Veterans and Military Families Month, President Joe Biden expresses gratitude to the members of the armed forces, their families, and caregivers for their vital contributions and sacrifices in safeguarding national security. He emphasizes the nation's obligation to properly equip and support troops during deployment and upon their return. The president acknowledges that military families play an integral role, enduring challenges and making sacrifices while their loved ones serve. He highlights the importance of supporting military families for the well-being of service members and national security. The administration's Joining Forces initiative focuses on addressing various aspects of military family support, such as employment, education, and health. The president calls upon the American people to honor veterans and military families through appropriate ceremonies and activities throughout November.